name: Escallonia 'Gold Ellen'
description: A compact, evergreen shrub to about 2m with small, shiny, yellow leaves with an irregular dark green splash in the centre. Clusters of small, dark pink flowers are produced in late summer

name: Evergreen 'Celina' Plant
description: A dwarf evergreen shrub to around 30cm high, with dark red-brown stems and narrow, glossy green leaves that are slightly toothed towards the tips. Palest lilac to near-white flowers are produced in clusters at the tips of the stems in late spring

name: Fuchsia 'Riccartonii'
description: A robust, upright, deciduous shrub to 2m in height, with small dark green leaves slightly bronzed. Small single flowers, with crimson tubes and sepals, and violet-purple corollas are produced in summer and autumn; ideal for hedging in frost-free locations

name: Euonymus Duc D'anjou
description: An upright, evergreen shrub with ovate, glossy variegated leaves which are serrated at the edges. Small, insignificant green flowers appear in late spring or early summer

name: Fuchsia 'Versicolor'
description: A deciduous shrub with small, grey-green leaves variably margined with cream and flushed pink when young; flowers slender, with red tube and sepals and purple petals

name: Garrya thurettii - Silk Tassle
description: 'James Roof' is a large vigorous bushy evergreen shrub with leathery dark green leaves. Flowers male, in drooping grey-green catkins to 20cm in length

name: Hebe andersonii Elsa
description: A large, evergreen shrub with narrowly oval, pointed leaves on dark stems. Long sprays of tiny, purple flowers, fading to white, are produced from mid-summer into autumn

name: Double Rose of Sharon Tree - Duc de Brabant
description: 'Duc de Brabant' forms a vase-shaped shrub to 3m tall with upright stems bearing large, double flowers ranging in colour from reddish-pink to purplish-red

name: Syriacus Blue Bird (Oiseau Bleu)
description: A medium-sized, upright deciduous shrub with lobed, dark green leaves. Single, violet-blue flowers with a maroon centre, to 8cm in width, appear in late summer and autumn

name: Syriacus Woodbridge - Pink Tree Hollyhock
description: A medium-sized, upright deciduous shrub with dark, lobed leaves. Flowers to 10cm in width, single, deep pink, with dark red centres

name: Hibiscus sinensis rosea 'Tivoli'
description: Bushy upright rose about 40-60cm tall, with glossy dark green leaves. Lightly scented, fully double, butter-yellow blooms 10-15cm across, borne singly on long stems, almost continuously in flower from early summer to early autumn

name: Japonica Polar Passion - Passion Frost - Evergreen
type: Pieris - Lily of the Valley Shrub
description: A compact, evergreen shrub with shiny, green foliage, pale when young, and large, drooping sprays of small, pink and white, urn-shaped flowers in mid-spring

name: Japonica Temple Bells
type: Pieris - Lily of the Valley Shrub
description: A slow-growing evergreen shrub, to around 1.5m high, with an upright habit and elliptic, slightly toothed, glossy green leaves that are deep red when young. Pendent clusters of relatively large, scented, urn-shaped white flowers are borne at the tips of the stems in spring

name: Japonica Little Heath - Evergreen
type: Pieris - Lily of the Valley Shrub
description: 'Little Heath' is a compact, rounded evergreen shrub with small, dark green leaves, coppery-red when young. Flowers few or none
